      "Description": "Job DescriptionPAE seeks a Deputy Chief of Party for the anticipated USAID-funded Improved Disaster Risk Management project in Nepal. This anticipated five-year project will support Nepal to strengthen its capacity to manage disasters as well as to strengthen institutions in a way that is inclusive, reliant on best practices and technological interventions, and adaptive to changing circumstances. We are looking for individuals who have a passion for making a difference in the lives of people around the world.  \n\n\nResponsibility for the operational implementation of the project under the direction of the COP \nAbility to act as COP in the COP’s absence \nCollaborate with PAE Corporate office to support the program updates \nStrong written and verbal communication skills, English fluency required \nStrong interpersonal/diplomatic skills and cultural/political sensitivity \nStrong institutional analytical and development skills Qualifications: \n\n\n\nSeven years of progressively responsible experience in managing project teams, experience with disaster risk management preferred and experience as a Chief of Party or Deputy Chief of Party preferred \nAt least a B.A. in Business Management, International Development or a related field of study is required; \nExperience with USAID-funded projects \nUnderstanding of USAID policies and procedures and compliance\nExperience managing grants under contract preferred \n\nResponsibilities include: \n\n Lead the operations of the project, including financial management, contracting, grants, administration, human resources, IT, and program activities and other support services as required  \nSupervise operations’ staff  \nSupport the COP’s leadership to provide strategic guidance, technical support, and management \nMaintain relationships with client, stakeholders, and partners under the direction of the COP \nSupport meeting program requirements and compliance",
