      "Image": "",
      "Description": "Job DescriptionDevelopment Director - Remote anywhere in the U.S.\nJob Purpose: \nReporting to and in partnership with the Executive Director, the Development Director creates and implements a strategic approach to fundraising. Fundraising opportunities may include major gifts, grants, and in-kind donations. Because he or she will occupy a new position in the organization, the Development Director will have the opportunity to exercise significant strategic vision.\nResponsibilities\n\nCollaborate with the Board of Directors and Executive Director to develop and execute GCCM’s fundraising plan. Set and achieve goals. Submit regular reports on progress toward goals to Board and Executive Director.\nWorking with a highly engaged network, identify and cultivate new funders and steward relationships with existing funders. Develop an understanding of individual funders’ interests and how GCCM fulfills them, and establish passionate relationships around GCCM’s mission and unique value.\nSecure financial support from individuals, foundations, and other institutions. Draft development plans and timelines; write development materials such as case statements and grants; contribute to funder reports and updates.\nIn collaboration with the Communications team, create and execute a digital fundraising strategy. Write solicitation and thank-you emails and donation pages, develop and implement plans for major online giving events such as Giving Tuesday, and create related digital material.\nIdentify and implement new opportunities to expand GCCM’s engagement with funders, such as the creation of special events, visits to compelling locations in our incredible global network, etc.\nManage the implementation of development software and oversee staff responsible for data entry and gift processing.\n\nRequired Qualifications\n\nMinimum 7 years of development/fundraising experience, with some experience in team management.\nDemonstrated record of success in meeting significant fundraising goals.\nDemonstrated knowledge of cultivation, solicitation, and stewardship strategies and techniques for institutional and individual funders.\nSuperior written and oral communication and presentation skills in English, to include experience speaking to and writing for donors and crafting compelling funding proposals and pitch materials.\nWillingness to travel to cultivate donor relationships, as needed.\nComfort working with a diverse global network, including demonstrated expertise in cultural diversity and ideally multilingual ability.\nStrong organizational skills and attention to detail.\nWorking knowledge of donor databases.\nPreferred background in environmental issues and working in a faith-based environment.\n\nSalary: Competitive $70,000 to $90,000 plus, depending on skills and experience\nBenefits: Medical, dental and PTO\nApplication Deadline: Rolling until hired\nStart Date: October 1, 2018 or sooner\nLocation: This is a remote position located anywhere in the United States. Candidate must possess his/her computer and have reliable access to the Internet. The candidate must also be comfortable participating in meetings that occur during the day in Rome.\nHow to apply: Send the following to jobs@catholicclimatemovement.global:\n1) Cover letter explaining your qualifications and interest in the role\n2) CV\n3) Two writing samples.\nApplicants that do not include all required documents will not be considered\nPut “Applicant: Development Director” in the subject line.",
      "About": "The Global Catholic Climate Movement is a community of Catholic institutions and individuals responding to the Pope’s call to action in the Laudato Si’ encyclical. We are lay people, priests, religious, bishops and a global network of partners working together on the climate change crisis, to protect God’s creation, the poor–who are the most vulnerable to climate disruption–and our children, who will face the worst impacts in the coming years."
