      "Description": "Job Description*Why CDM Smith?\nCDM Smith provides lasting and integrated solutions in water, environment, transportation, energy and facilities to public and private clients worldwide. As a full-service consulting, engineering, construction, and operations firm, we deliver exceptional client service, quality results and enduring value across the entire project life cycle.\n\nTo learn more about CDM Smith and our work with International Development please visit us at:\n\nhttps://www.cdmsmith.com/en/Client-Solutions/Focus-Areas/Development-Assistance\n\n\n\n*Job Description\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe overall objective of the project, of which this service contract will be a part, is to build, rehabilitate and modernise municipal water sector infrastructure in the City of Kutaisi. Purpose of the project The purpose of this service contract will be to assist the Contracting Authority in preparation and implementation of the Kutaisi Wastewater Project by preparation of designs and works tender documentations, and by supervision of construction & commissioning of the WWTP and sewerage network with associated objects and constructions. Job Responsibilities:The Team Leader shall be responsible for the overall service contract management throughout the design, procurement, implementation, commissioning trial run and DNP, i.e., from the commencement to the end date of the Consultancy Contract, s/he shall manage design and supervision teams, coordinate all activities, and closely cooperate with the Promoter and its PIU for project management. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n*Minimum Qualifications\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQualifications and skills• Master’s degree in Civil Engineering or equivalent, with specialisation in wastewater engineering or a related engineering discipline• Fluent in written and spoken English• Knowledge of local language or Russian will be an advantage• Proficient user of (Microsoft) Office software and Project Management Software (Microsoft Project Manager, Primavera etc. • Proficiency in design software (Auto CAD, 3D Auto desk or Bentley (e.g. Civil 3D, or Plant 3D, or Auto Cad 3D, or Sewer Gems, etc.) will be an advantageGeneral professional experience• Minimum 15 years of professional experience in water sector (water, wastewater, drainage) • Minimum 10 years’ experience in team management of multi-component projects in water and/or wastewater sector• Minimum 2 years of experience in urban infrastructure projects in Georgia and/or CIS countrySpecific professional experience• Minimum of 5 years as Team Leader/Project Manager for WWTP and/or sewerage design experience; • Design experience in minimum 2 projects including WWTP(s) with a capacity of more than 200,000 population equivalents with an investment cost more than 10 million EUR;• Minimum of 5 years of experience as FIDIC Engineer for WWTP and/or sewerage construction projects; • Supervision experience in minimum 2 projects including WWTP(s) with a capacity of more than 200,000 population equivalents with an investment cost more than 10 million EUR.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n*Agency Disclaimer\nAll vendors must have a signed CDM Smith Placement Agreement from the CDM Smith Recruitment Center Manager to receive payment for your placement. Verbal or written commitments from any other member of the CDM Smith staff will not be considered binding terms. All unsolicited resumes sent to CDM Smith and any resume submitted to any employee outside of CDM Smith Recruiting Center Team (RCT) will be considered property of CDM Smith. CDM Smith will not be held liable to pay a placement fee.\n\nWe attract the best people in the industry, supporting their efforts to learn and grow. We strive to create a challenging and progressive work environment. We provide career opportunities that span a variety of disciplines and geographic locations, with projects that our employees plan, design, build and operate—as diverse as the needs of our clients. CDM Smith is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action employer.  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, disability, or protected veteran status.\n\nQualified candidates should clicking on the link below: \n\nhttps://sjobs.brassring.com/TGnewUI/Search/home/HomeWithPreLoad?PageType=JobDetails&partnerid=25038&siteid=5220&areq=21491BR",
