      "Description": "Job DescriptionDexis is seeking an experienced Program Analyst to provide support and expertise to the United States Agency for International Development (USAID), Asia Bureau/AMS office. The work for this position will be based in Washington, D.C. This is a short-term position. The start date is immediate.\n\n\n\nResponsibilities \n\n\n\n\nProvide administrative and program support to the Administrative Management Staff team in USAID’s Asia Bureau\nSupport management activities, such as personnel and organization management, security, awards, performance management, and other aspects of administrative and logistical support\nPlan, design, and implement processes to improve systems and procedures\nEnsure records are kept current and are published to appropriate systems\nDraft correspondence and reports related to managing administrative programs and issues\nIdentify and analyze opportunities for training, and develops recommendations as appropriate\nOther tasks as designated by technical team leaders\n\n\n\n\nQualifications \n\n\n\n\nBachelor’s degree in relevant field (international affairs, political science, public policy, international development, communications, etc.)\nMinimum of 3 years of professional work experience\nDemonstrated knowledge of development programs, especially in the Asia region preferred\nProven experience in project administration\nProficient in the use of Windows, Microsoft Office, Internet search engines, database and email applications\nExperience with USAID preferred\nSecret-level clearance required\n\n\nDexis is an equal opportunity employer offering employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, age, national origin, citizenship, physical or mental handicap, or status as a disabled or Vietnam Era veteran of the US Armed Forces.",
      "About": "Since 2001, Dexis has provided innovative management solutions for a secure and prosperous world.   In the last three years alone, Dexis has worked in 90 countries supporting critical missions of agencies in the global development and security assistance space.  With triple digit growth in recent years, Dexis was ranked in the top 10 consulting firms by funding at the US Agency for International Development in FY16 and FY17.  Dexis was also among the highest rated employers on Glassdoor, where many of its 250-plus employees cited a people-centered leadership and culture as the main drivers to its success."
