      "Description": "Job DescriptionTitle: Manager, Development and Partner Engagement\nReports to: Director, Development and Partner Engagement\nClassification: Full-time\nLocation: New York, NY\nStart Date: Immediate\n \n\nSummary:\nWomen’s World Banking is seeking an experienced fundraiser responsible for the cultivation, solicitation and stewardship for a diverse portfolio of corporations, foundations and bi/multi-lateral agencies. In addition, manages a portfolio of restricted and unrestricted funding annually and maintaining a schedule of contacts.\n\nResponsibilities: \n\nDevelops and maintains a donor base and partnerships (corporations, foundations, bi/multi-laterals, NGOs, etc) by researching organizations in relevant markets for alignment and resources to pursue, making initial contact with organizations and “selling” Women’s World Banking\nProvide a powerful message to ensure donations, grants and gifts are received\nDevelops and implements pipeline growth strategy supported by relevant research and action plan\nDevelops and manages documentation by producing quality concept notes/grant proposals including the internal review of documents and preparing final documents for submission in coordination with the Proposal Writer\nMonitors overall activity by managing the existing grants calendar, tracking grant reporting requirements, monitoring and managing grant award processes and overseeing preparation of required progress reports in coordination with the staff Compliance team.\nParticipates in cross-functional teams by working with Marketing & Communications to effectively communicate the brand identity and Women’s World Banking’s value proposition to donors\nWorking with Event staff to secure corporation, foundation participation and sponsorship, working with Programs to develop proposal content and donor reports\n\nRequired Qualifications:\n\nBachelor’s degree in a business/international relations discipline\nA minimum of 5 years’ experience in direct business development or fundraising with demonstrated track record of successfully achieving fundraising targets\nStrong interpersonal, organization, problem-solving, planning and multi-tasking skills are required.\nStrong computer literacy (word processing, spreadsheet, database, SalesForce) also required.\n\n\nAbility to work collaboratively and interact effectively with people of other cultures, abilities and socio-economic backgrounds\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills. Ability to speak eloquently to a wide variety of audiences about our work\nAbility to work deal with stress, high pressure and tight deadlines\n\n \nPreferred Qualifications: \n\nFluency in Spanish, Arabic, and/or French.\n\nSuccess\nWithin the first 75 days:\n\nEmbrace Women’s World Banking’s core values and desired behaviors;\nEmbrace Women’s World Banking’s unique characteristics and offerings to be able to market them to potential donors and sponsors\nLearn and comprehend the Women’s World Banking brand, business model, and financial needs\nUse priority markets identified in the corporate strategy to complete significant research in identifying new partners and donors, feeding into the fundraising strategy\nBecome trained and fully integrated in the use of Salesforce and other systems\nEstablish and strengthen existing relationships with current partners\nDevelop opportunities for strategic alliance, joint initiatives and public-private partnerships",
      "About": "We believe in being a force for the greater good, devoted to accelerating and growing the financial inclusion of women. With rapidly changing markets, influenced by technology and social behavioral expectations, we are embarking on a new chapter to transform the way we design and implement solutions."
