      "Image": "https://res.cloudinary.com/devex/image/fetch/c_fill,w_140/https://neo-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/assets/0129/7677/download%2520%25281%2529.png",
      "Description": "Job DescriptionPosition Summary: Creative seeks an experienced Operation Manager for an anticipated USAID-funded Somalia education project. The Operations Manager will be responsible for overseeing the smooth running of the head and regional offices and ensuring that office operations are kept consistent with donor and project standards. The Operations Manager will supervise and be responsible for overall security, logistics, procurement, ICT, and other office administration functions for the project.\nReporting & Supervision:\nThe Operations Manager will report to the Director of Finance and Operations and will be based in Mogadishu.\nPrimary Responsibilities:\n\nProvide strategic management to the IT, Administration, Security, and Logistics functions of the overall program;\nWork with regional Operations Officers to ensure that all regional offices; operational policies, including security, procurement, inventory and IT, are in place, compliant with project and client policies, and implemented effectively;\nEnsure a coordinated approach to, IT, Administration, Security, and Logistics across all the regions of responsibility;\nEnsure that project operations are in line with one another, liaising regularly with Operations Officers in regional offices;\nTravel as needed to regional offices to ensure smooth and harmonized operations, providing management support as necessary;\nAssist in the review of the regional office operational budget and strategic plans;\nOversee operations team to ensure that procurement management is done on planned, timely manner and fleet management is well organized and coordinated with all sectors; and\nAssist the Director of Finance and Operations with other duties as needed.\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n\nBachelor’s degree required, preferably in logistics, administration or related field, with demonstrated experience in logistics and administration in Somalia;\nAt least six (6) years of progressive experience with at least four (4) years’ experience with an international NGO in the areas of operations and logistics;\nComprehensive knowledge of operations and logistics systems and procedures donor/client-funded projects in Somalia;\nExcellent teamwork including abilities to coordinate well with diverse individuals and teams and to negotiate effectively with colleagues and stakeholders to achieve results;\nPrevious experience working in USAID-funded programs preferred;\nStrong communication skills, both oral and written; and\nFluency in English and Somali is required.\n\nLocal candidates strongly encouraged to apply.\nPosition contingent upon donor funding.",
      "About": "Creative Associates International is a dynamic, fast-growing global development firm that specializes in education, economic growth, democratic development and post-crisis stabilization. Based in Washington, D.C., Creative has a field presence in more than 25 countries with a strong client portfolio that includes the U.S. Agency for International Development and the State Department, among others. Since its founding in 1977, Creative has earned a solid reputation among its clients and is well-regarded by competitors and partners alike."
