      "Description": "Job DescriptionThe Communications and Knowledge Management (KM) Specialist will provide technical leadership and management oversight for all strategic communications and knowledge management activities.  S/he will support the planning and execution of strategic communications and knowledge management planning, audience analysis, and content design and production for the project. S/he will also coordinate with other (national/regional) stakeholders to organize, consolidate, and communicate lessons. The Communications and KM Specialist will also provide guidance on promoting learning to further the project’s conservation and mitigation efforts.\nQualifications:\n\nBachelor’s degree or higher in a field related to international development, organizational development, knowledge management, business administration, or a similar focus.\nA least 7 years of demonstrated expertise in strategic communications, public advocacy, and behavior change, particularly in relation to international development.\nExperience working in the sectors of environmental protection and climate change, especially in the Amazon region.\nDemonstrated expertise in knowledge management, curation, and evidence aggregation.\nA demonstrated track record of success in managing communications activities and outreach campaigns, including developing excellent collaborative working relationships with partners and other stakeholders.\nFluency in Spanish and English required; Portuguese preferred.\nExperience working in the Latin America and Caribbean region.",
