      "Description": "Job DescriptionPOSITION DESCRIPTION\nThe Asia Foundation, a non-profit international development organization committed to improving lives across a dynamic and developing Asia, seeks an experienced elections specialist to serve as a Dhaka-based Interim Team Leader for a domestic election observation program in Bangladesh. The Interim Team Leader will oversee the Foundation’s  support for long-term and short-term observation of Bangladesh’s 11th Parliamentary Elections by the Election Working Group, a network of Bangladeshi organizations, and will run from approximately late September 2018 through February 2019. The Interim Team Leader will be responsible for providing overall vision, leadership, and guidance for the program, and will report to the Country Representative. Qualified national and international candidates are strongly encouraged to apply.\nSUMMARY OF JOB RESPONSIBILITIES\n\nServe as the primary point of contact with program funders for procedural and substantive matters;\nBe responsible for quality control of the technical aspects of performance, personnel, reporting, and other management-related requirements of the program;\nProvide technical leadership for long-term and short-term observation activities;\nCoordinate with and manage relationships with funder counterparts in Dhaka, including meeting and consulting regularly with funders regarding the program’s performance and direction;\nSupervise a team of professionals and experts  \n\nREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\nRelevant advanced degree in international development, social science, public policy, or a related field of study;\nMinimum of ten years’ progressively responsible experience in international development, with at least five years of senior managerial-level experience in a developing country, preferably in Asia;\nDemonstrated success in managing and implementing long- and short-term election observation programs, and working with various stakeholders, including government;\nExpert knowledge and understanding of issues related to election observation, the electoral environment, and electoral procedures;\nExcellent oral and written communication skills in English.\nPast experience working in Bangladesh, and knowledge of Bangla highly preferred.    \n\nInterested applicants should submit a cover letter and CV by September 20, 2018 to psds.consultants@asiafoundation.org with the position listed in the subject line. The Asia Foundation is an equal opportunity employer. No phone calls, please.",
      "About": "The Asia Foundation is a nonprofit international development organization committed to improving lives across a dynamic and developing Asia. Informed by six decades of experience and deep local expertise, our work across the region addresses five overarching goals—strengthen governance, empower women, expand economic opportunity, increase environmental resilience, and promote regional cooperation."
